<DocsLayout title="Tool Reference" description="Complete reference for all 24 LeanCTX MCP tools, organized by category." sidebar={sidebar}>
  <p>LeanCTX provides 24 MCP tools organized into four categories. Each tool is used by the AI automatically — you don't need to learn or type any of these commands.</p>

  <h2 id="core-tools">Core Tools — File & Code</h2>
  <p>
    The foundation. These handle file reading, directory exploration, command execution, and code search — the operations that make up 90% of AI coding interactions.
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Tool</th><th>What it does</th><th>Savings</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><a href="/docs/tools/core#ctx_read"><code>ctx_read</code></a></td><td>Smart file read with 6 compression modes + session caching</td><td>up to 99%</td></tr>
      <tr><td><a href="/docs/tools/core#ctx_multi_read"><code>ctx_multi_read</code></a></td><td>Batch file reads in one call</td><td>fewer round-trips</td></tr>
      <tr><td><a href="/docs/tools/core#ctx_tree"><code>ctx_tree</code></a></td><td>Compact project structure maps</td><td>34-60%</td></tr>
      <tr><td><a href="/docs/tools/core#ctx_shell"><code>ctx_shell</code></a></td><td>Shell commands with 90+ pattern compression</td><td>60-95%</td></tr>
      <tr><td><a href="/docs/tools/core#ctx_search"><code>ctx_search</code></a></td><td>Regex code search with compact results</td><td>50-80%</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p><a href="/docs/tools/core">View full Core Tools documentation →</a></p>

