    Tools that go beyond compression — they understand your workflow, detect intent, deduplicate context, and intelligently manage token budgets.
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Tool</th><th>What it does</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><a href="/docs/tools/intelligence#ctx_smart_read"><code>ctx_smart_read</code></a></td><td>Auto-selects optimal compression mode based on file context</td></tr>
      <tr><td><a href="/docs/tools/intelligence#ctx_delta"><code>ctx_delta</code></a></td><td>Incremental file update — only sends changed hunks</td></tr>
      <tr><td><a href="/docs/tools/intelligence#ctx_fill"><code>ctx_fill</code></a></td><td>Priority-based context filling with a token budget</td></tr>
      <tr><td><a href="/docs/tools/intelligence#ctx_intent"><code>ctx_intent</code></a></td><td>Semantic intent detection + auto file loading</td></tr>
      <tr><td><a href="/docs/tools/intelligence#ctx_context"><code>ctx_context</code></a></td><td>Multi-turn context state overview</td></tr>
      <tr><td><a href="/docs/tools/intelligence#ctx_graph"><code>ctx_graph</code></a></td><td>Persistent project dependency graph (build, related, symbol, impact)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><a href="/docs/tools/intelligence#ctx_dedup"><code>ctx_dedup</code></a></td><td>Cross-file deduplication analysis</td></tr>
      <tr><td><a href="/docs/tools/intelligence#ctx_response"><code>ctx_response</code></a></td><td>Bi-directional response compression</td></tr>
      <tr><td><a href="/docs/tools/intelligence#ctx_discover"><code>ctx_discover</code></a></td><td>Shell history analysis for missed compression opportunities</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
